On Sun, 19 Oct 2003, Access Systems wrote:

> On Sun, 19 Oct 2003, daniel nelson wrote:

> > I had my brake booster rebuilt by H & R Auto Parts Rebuilders of Dallas TX
> > and now when I brake the idle increases....brake power is reduced. Is the
> > booster going out again? I checked for leaks in the hoses and they all seem
> > good. This is on my 71 Westy that I have a sale pending on.

> is the one way valve on backwards.  you should be able to suck on the
> valve from the engine side but not the booster side.

If the 1-way valve was on backwards, the engine would definitely not have
a problem with vacuum leaks!  The booster would also not see any vacuum,
causing the power brakes not to work.

Since the problem is only when the brakes are applied, it certainly sounds
like a vacuum leak in the booster.

George Lyle
